give @s written_book{pages:['["",{"text":"Bridging and Building Under the Island","color":"dark_blue","clickEvent":{"action":"run_command","value":"/function give_a_book:table_of_contents"}},{"text":"\\nWhile you are sneaking, the game won\\u2019t let you walk off of the edge of a block. You can use this to hang off the side of the island safely and place more blocks. If you keep repeating this in one direction it is called \\u2018bridging\\u2019.","color":"reset"}]','{"text":"The best block to use for bridging is any kind of slab block. It\\u2019s more efficient with your limited blocks and if you bridge using the bottom half of a block then mobs can\\u2019t spawn there, keeping your bridges safe without needing torches."}','{"text":"If you want to build lower than the starting island then there is a way to do it. If this is your first time trying this, then you should put any important items in a safe place in case you mess up and fall into the void. You first want to let some water flow off the side of your island."}','{"text":"From there you can swim in the water stream and float down below the island placing blocks as you go down. You should be able to swim around to the side and make a platform to stand on."}'],title:"Technical Skyblock Guidebook",author:"Procymbopteryx and Kitty_McTophat",display:{Lore:['{"text":"Bridging and Building Under the Island"}']}}
